news.title: Ahmedabad: FIR filed after Pacifica Infraplus LLP reneges on amenities
news.para: According to the FIR filed with Vastrapur police, Pacifica Infraplus LLP launched a housing scheme in 2019 at Sterling City in Bopal. The scheme had 23 bungalows with a construction areas of 300 to 350 square metres each.

news.title: Complete deficient infrastructure work in Ansal Esencia: Haryana RERA
news.para: Following this, the real estate watchdog directed the developer to ensure that the necessary infrastructure is built soon. They also warned of legal consequences if any violations of the direction are found.

news.title: Aditya Birla Sun Life AMC partners BentallGreenOak
news.para: The fund, including a green-shoe option worth up to ₹250 crore, will be investing in real estate projects in key property markets including metro cities.

news.title: Delhi government likely to extend rebate on circle rate by six months
news.para: The rebate scheme was launched in February 2021 to revive the economy and help people hit by the impact of the COVID-19-induced lockdown. It was extended till June 30 by the government in December last year.

news.title: Supertech plans to raise around Rs 300 crore to expedite construction at its ongoing projects
news.para: "The company has tied up with investors to accelerate construction ... The company has in hand investment offers of approximately Rs 300 crore which would help them to augment construction and delivery," Supertech said.

news.title: S&P Global downgrades developer Greenland Holdings to 'selective default'
news.para: Shanghai-based Greenland is the first state-backed developer to extend a dollar-bond payment since the country's property sector plunged into a debt crisis last year.

news.title: CREDAI Gujarat to employ 3,000 Agniveers
news.para: The Agniveers will get a monthly salary of Rs 30,000 to Rs 40,000, with 75% of them who get demobilized after four years getting a ‘Seva Nidhi’ exit package of Rs 11.71 lakh, half of which will be through their own contributions.

news.title: UP-RERA de-registers three housing projects in Ghaziabad over work delay
news.para: ​The registrations of Antriksh Sanskriti Phase-2, Antriksh Sanskriti Phase-3 and Raksha Vigyaan Sanskriti Phase-2 have been cancelled and proceedings initiated under RERA's Section 8, the real estate regulatory authority said.

news.title: CBI books DHFL, its former CMD and director in Rs 34,615 crore bank fraud
news.para: ​Following the registration of case, a team of over 50 officials from the agency carried out coordinated searches in Mumbai at 12 locations belonging to listed accused in the FIR which also includes Sudhakar Shetty of Amaryllis Realtors and eight other builders.

news.title: Conduct fire safety audit of buildings: Haryana chief secretary
news.para: The CS directed the officials to conduct a special fire safety audit of cinema halls and multiplexes operating across the state soon. Similarly, fire safety audits will be carried out in universities as well

news.title: Over 10 lakh in Uttar Pradesh to get property papers under Swamitva scheme
news.para: Under the Swamitva scheme, the government is preparing ownership documents for rural residents in all 75 districts. It has identified 1,10,313 villages for which documents have to be prepared.

news.title: Gujarat: 2,429 cases of property attachment pending with district magistrates
news.para: According to the latest report by the State Level Bankers’ Committee (SLBC), 2,429 cases filed by banks seeking nod for attachment of properties are pending. This is costing the banks recovery to the tune of Rs 1,157 crore.

news.title: Government allows registration of Telangana Housing Board joint venture projects
news.para: The respite comes after GO No 1061, which was issued in May 2016, came into force recently after the Telangana Housing Board issued a letter dated May 7, 2022, to developers of over a dozen JV projects granting permission to proceed with registration formalities.

news.title: Telangana: High bid for Rajiv Swagruha plots, auction fetches Rs 15.3 crore
news.para: As many as 45 plots were sold and 190 bidders participated. The highest bid was Rs 19,000 per square yard and the lowest Rs 8,100 for one of the plots in the township.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Property sale deeds under reassessment not online yet
news.para: The new system module, through which the documents can be uploaded online, was made available to the deputy collectors’ offices on June 8.
